{"key":"processedPost-12728864","value":{"id":12728864,"first":12728443,"last":12731011,"when":1276316426,"utime":"06/12/10 07:20 AM","content":"All of the above is correct and just to add, the intensity of light is reduced by the square of the distance as you move the light away.&nbsp; In other words if you move a light from 12\" away from the tub to 24\" away, you cut the light to 1/4 the amount.&nbsp; If you move it from 12\" away to 36\" away, you cut the amount of light to 1/9 what it was before.&nbsp; That's why you want the light as close as you can without causing excess heat buildup.&nbsp; Light from the sides is just as good as light from above.&nbsp; In fact, the sides of a terrarium in the middle of a room can bring in much more light, considering they're 80% of the surface area, vs only 20% for the top.(assuming the tub is a cube for simplicity).<br />RR","title":"Re: Lighting","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}